    "description": "An onlay is a covering that encases part(s) of a tooth surface(s) restoring it to its original shape and size; this restoration protects and strengthens tooth structure. An onlay is diagnosed, when a tooth is too far broken down to be restored by a filling and yet not broken down far enough to be restored by a crown (cap).",
